8/12 : we live in a simulation theory
1.what is this?
      it suggest that everything we see touch, feel , and experience might not be the "real world", but a computer -generated simulation created by an advanced civilization 
   this idea isn't new.many philosophers throughout history have asked similar questions

1.ancient roots of the idea 
 plato- allegory of the cave : 
       -people live chained inside a cave
       - they only see shadows on a wall
       - they believed the shadow are reality 
       - in truth, the shadows are just projections from objects behind them 

