SHOULD THE SCHOOL TEACH CHILRDEN PRATICAL SKILLS OR JUST ACADEMIC KNOWLEDGE?
  Schools should also teach practical skills such as money management, communication, and basic life skills for daily living.
  Practical skills help students become independent and confident in real-life situations.
  Learning both academic and practical skills helps students be better prepared for future jobs.
  Therefore, schools should teach both academic knowledge and practical skills to give students a balanced education.
